	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f98648199689127>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Pally Helmets & Armor</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Apr 5th 10:46 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I need some armor advice.&nbsp;&nbsp;And Paladin advice.<br><br>I have what I hope is a healthy pride in my appearance, and I'd like to show to anyone who passes by at a glance, that I'm a paladin.  Due to the rarity, I haven't seen or been able to find a picture of an Erudite Paladin. (Truthfully I'm not completely sure what to look for.)  Do we also get the winged helmets?<br><br>I'm a low level, casual player, so I do get helpful offers from my frequently playing friends. Offers (which are never asked for, humbly accepted, and GREATLY appreciated; praise be to Quellios) for encouragement and as reward for acts of kindness. <br><br>I have a couple offers of helmets, but I don't want to have anyone go to unnecessary trouble getting one to me.  I have been offered leather, bronze (which seems like it would be heavy), and chainmail/banded.  Does anyone know how these look on Erudite/Paladins?<br><br>Also for the future, is there a notable or distinctive armor that I should purchase or quest for as a paladin?<br><br>I was asked recently by a well-wisher whom I'd given assistance, if there was anything I needed.  I didn't chose paladin to be greedy, so responded with "I live only to serve."  But in all seriousness as a totally, novice gamer.... IS there anything that I "need"?<br><br>Dnahri<br>4th level Erudite-Paladin<br>The Nameless</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
