	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Whatever you do, DO NOT forget to practive 1HS.&nbsp;&nbsp;When I was your level, I was so impressed by the way I looked with a 1HS and a shield.  So I didn't even pick up a 2HS weapon till level 18.  I paid dearly for this mistake.  Remember that our epics are 2HS weapons and the longer you let 2HS skilling slide, the harder it will be.  I am about to get my Soulfire soon thanks to my guild members.  But it will be useless if I don't practice 2HS more.  It is important to keep your DEX up when you are skilling in a melee skill.  As you move along in the game, don't forget to buy dex, wis, int, and str jewelry if you see a steal of a deal.  Before going into battle or practicing a skill, swap out jewelry to enhance your stats according to what you are doing.  <br>As for armor?  I am a blacksmith by trade so I would have to go with banded.  Banded looks pretty sweet and for the money/ac, it is well worth buying.  Of course, I will tell anyone to start blacksmithing as a trade skill.  Right now, I am a 21 level Paladin with all the following items bought with money made from blacksmithing:<br><br>Ghoulbane(1HS)- Oh yeah, this is a beauty <br>Velium Round Shield- with 15AC and .5 weight, how can anyone go wrong (remember AC is KING)<br>Axe of the Frost(2HS)- 20dmg/45dly I am saving this one for when it procs "Shock of Frost" at level 25<br>Numerous WIS, INT, DEX, STR items<br>and a Full Suit of Fine Plate Armor Dyed 2 resin Yellow (made this set personally)<br><br>Good Luck to you.  Hope this helps.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
